Galen H. WELCH, Former Collector of Internal Revenue for the Sixth District of California, v. Edwin J. GRANT et al. No. 8878. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 27, 1938. Ben Harrison, U. S. Atty., and E. H. Mitchell and Armond Monroe Jewell, Asst. U. S. Attys., all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Claude I. Parker and Bayley Kohlmeier, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellees.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
